# iCloud Tagger
> Auto-generated by /project-context | Last updated: 2026-03-06

## Goals & Strategy
A Python tool (v2) that automatically tags files in iCloud Drive using macOS Finder color tags and custom tags. Optimized with batched tag operations (~100x faster than per-file tagging). Also creates a `~/Creative-Assets/` alias/symlink folder structure organized by workflow category.

**Who:** Elad Tzur (personal productivity tool)
**Why:** Organize a large iCloud Drive (~46,000+ files) with consistent Finder tags for easy filtering and retrieval. Tags span content type (Photo, Document, Video, etc.), context/project (Business, Finance, Lecture, Podcast, etc.), and technical properties (Hi-Res, Lo-Res, Transparent, raw).

## Architecture & Tech Stack
- Language: Python 3 (659 lines)
- External CLI dependency: `tag` (brew install tag) — macOS Finder tag management
- Optional: `Pillow` (PIL) — image analysis for resolution/transparency detection
- No pip packages beyond Pillow
- Phases:
  1. Collect: Walk iCloud Drive, compute tag sets per file
  2. Apply: Batch apply tags via `tag` CLI (BATCH_SIZE=50)
  3. Aliases: Create ~/Creative-Assets/ symlink structure

